cars.name: Ford Mustang
cars.description: The Ford Mustang is an American car manufactured by Ford. It was originally based on the platform of the second generation North American Ford Falcon, a compact car.

cars.name: Chevrolet Camaro
cars.description: The Chevrolet Camaro is a mid-size American automobile manufactured by Chevrolet, classified as a pony car and some versions also as a muscle car.

cars.name: Dodge Challenger
cars.description: The Dodge Challenger is the name of three different generations of automobiles produced by American automobile manufacturer Dodge.

cars.name: Porsche 911
cars.description: The Porsche 911 is a two-door, 2+2 high performance rear-engined sports car made since 1963 by Porsche AG of Stuttgart, Germany.

cars.name: Maserati GranTurismo
cars.description: The Maserati GranTurismo is a grand tourer produced by the Italian automobile manufacturer Maserati.

cars.name: Audi R8
cars.description: The Audi R8 is a mid-engine, 2-seater sports car, which uses Audi's trademark quattro permanent all-wheel drive system.

cars.name: BMW M3
cars.description: The BMW M3 is a high-performance version of the BMW 3 Series, developed by BMW's in-house motorsport division, BMW M GmbH.

cars.name: Mercedes-Benz SLS AMG
cars.description: The Mercedes-Benz SLS AMG is a front-engine, 2-seater luxury sports car developed by the Mercedes-AMG division of German automotive manufacturer Mercedes-Benz.

cars.name: Lamborghini Aventador
cars.description: The Lamborghini Aventador is a mid-engine sports car produced by the Italian automotive manufacturer Lamborghini.
